# FS25 / GIANTS engine — FarmHub project grounding

## Single-thread & `g_currentMission`

- Game Lua is **single-threaded**. Long work in one `update(dt)` **blocks the sim** (stutter / hitch).
- **Never** walk deep into `g_currentMission` or serialize whole engine graphs to JSON. Build **small plain tables** (numbers, strings, shallow nested dicts/lists) for export only.
- **OOM risk** comes from deep traversal + huge strings, not from “having JSON” per se. Aggregate in Lua (totals, counts, flags) before JSON.

## Farmlands vs fields / density maps

- **Farmland** = economy / ownership tile (`farmlandId`, buy/sell in PDA). Use it for **who owns** bales, land, and dashboard ownership filters.
- **Field / crop state** = **density maps** (bit channels per world cell). Read via engine helpers (`DensityMapHeightUtil`, `DensityMapFilterLua`, field probes) at **sampled** X/Z — not `field.getCrop()` as a single scalar.
- **Dashboard JSON must not** ship large coordinate dumps (windrows, weeds). Export **aggregates** (e.g. `windrowLiters`, `baleCountOnField`, booleans), not hundreds of `(x,z)` points — large arrays bloat the file and slow the desktop merge on every write.

## Mod export loop (this repo)

- **`FarmDashboard.lua`**: `g_currentMission:addUpdateable`, **`isAuthority()`** — writes **SP + MP host/dedicated only**; MP clients skip export (arrays may be nil / stale).
- **`FarmDashboardDataCollector.lua`**: **Staggered collectors** over `collectionCycleMs` (default **60s**), **one module per slice** — avoids one-frame megascan.
- **Writes**: `modSettings/FS25_FarmDashboard/<saveSlot>/data.json` (+ `saveFile` fallback); **`toJSON`** is custom (no `json.encode`).
- **`FieldDataCollector.lua`**: heavy paths wrapped in **`pcall`** (mod conflicts / API differences).

## Mod conflicts & MP testing

- Third-party mods (e.g. **Precision Farming**, rotation extensions) can **replace or wrap** density / filter APIs. **Always `pcall`** density and filter calls; on failure **skip that metric** and keep the game running.
- **Test new export logic in single-player first**, then MP host; do not rely on full state on MP **client**.

## Known gaps / hardening (when touching Lua export)

- **`toJSON` has no max depth or cycle detection** — only safe if every collector outputs **acyclic plain data**. If adding new fields, never stash **userdata**, **function**, or **engine object references** in the assembled table.
- Prefer extending existing **aggregate-first** patterns in collectors over new per-point arrays.

## Dashboard merge (Node)

- **Prune** heavy keys where practical. Field rules and UI copy must not assume mechanics FS25 does not expose (e.g. parcel soil moisture / irrigation) unless the mod actually exports them.
